# Git workflow (Gestalt)

Always **`git fetch origin`** first, then integrate latest **`main`** with **`git pull origin main`** before any of the following. Resolve conflicts before continuing.

## When to run it

1. **Before creating a new branch** — Check out `main`, run `git pull origin main`, then `git checkout -b <new-branch>`. New work should branch from up-to-date `main`.

2. **Before pushing commits** — On your feature branch, run `git pull origin main` (merges `main` into the branch) or rebase onto updated `main` if the team prefers that. Do not push a branch that should track `main` without having integrated latest `main` first.

3. **Before opening or updating a pull request** — Same as (2): `git fetch origin` and `git pull origin main` on the PR branch so the PR is current and conflicts are caught locally.

## Quick sequence (typical feature branch)

```bash
git fetch origin
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout <your-branch>   # or: git checkout -b <new-branch>
git pull origin main           # when already on the feature branch, before push / gh pr create
```

If not allowed to change branch (dirty tree), at minimum **`git fetch origin`** then **`git pull origin main`** on the current branch before push or `gh pr create`.

## Shell for `gh`

Use **`./scripts/gh`** from the repo root (Homebrew on `PATH`) and wrap in **`bash -lc '…'`** when **`GH_TOKEN`** only loads from Bash — see **`.cursor/rules/pull-requests.mdc`**.
